        "translation": "\"The three buddhas of the ten directions, Amitâbha, the first of nine classes, who has saved sentient beings, whose virtue is limitless, now I make a great profession of reverence, confess the sins of three activities, and wholeheartedly dedicate myself to the memory of the Buddha. May those who join in the mindfulness of the Buddha's name have their responses manifest at any time, and when they reach their final destination in the West, their vision is clearly present, and they are all diligent in seeing and hearing the Buddha and being born in the Land of Perfect Bliss, seeing him as the Buddha who has ended birth and death, stopping unlimited afflictions, cultivating measureless teachings, vowing to save sentient beings, and vowing to achieve the Buddha Way in general.",
